ht|i|va|6|cs|6|at|^B{|ia|,1sp2np4np5cp5dp?|at|} ^mBoard 17 |HT|i|cs|1|at|^p{|ih|pSA7653HQ87DK5CK5|at|}|ht|o|at|^rSouth Hand|hf|O|cq||lb|*BNow, what bid would you make?^^6c|HT|Q|cp|8|AT|
^B@2^Y@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||fp||at|6@C is the correct answer. In this case, having the 5th spade is as good as having the Queen of trumps. Because you know you have ten trumps between you. You only promised 4 trumps with the 2N bid, but you have 5. And since you have the A and K and a 10 card fit, the Queen will drop most of the time, when the suit breaks 2-1. So, you respond positively to the Queen ask when you either have the Queen of trumps or extra trump length.
